newsitem.title: TAIWAN: Taiwan money rates close up, seen stable.
newsitem.headline: Taiwan money rates close up, seen stable.

text.p: Taiwan's money rates closed slightly higher on Monday amid expected routine monthly payroll demand, but dealers said banking system liquidity remained loose and that they did not expect major gains.
The overnight interbank rate ended at 4.645 percent against Saturday's 4.635 close, with 30-day commercial paper at 4.70-4.75 percent against 4.75-4.80.
Dealers said they expected the interbank rate to stabilise around 4.75 percent before the Finance Ministry's T$35 billion government bond auction on November 11.
The government bond market did not report any trade in the afternoon.
Traders said they expected bond yields to consolidate in coming sessions after having fallen in previous days.
